This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on the problem of training federated learning algorithms. It also involves optimization of an FL loss function, which is a common task in machine learning. 

The paper also deals with wireless networks, which suggests that it could belong to the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). 

The optimization problem formulated in the paper involves resource allocation, which could place it in the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). 

The joint learning and wireless resource allocation problem could also be classified under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). 

Finally, the paper involves the use of optimization techniques to solve a complex problem, which could place it in the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
